#text=I bought a tree from my local plant supply store .
#text=It was a small sapling with only a few branches on it .
#text=I took a shovel out of my garage and found a good place for the tree next to my house .
#text=I began digging a hole with the shovel for a few minutes until the hole was about one and a half feet deep .
#text=I set down the shovel , and removed the plastic wrap from the tree 's roots .
#text=I separated the roots and loosened them apart .
#text=I set the tree down into the hole , and used the shovel to fill in the space around the roots with dirt and fertilizer that would help the tree grow better .
#text=Then , I took a bag of mulch from out of the garage and spread some of it around the tree to help protect it from other invasive plants .
#text=I watered the tree with a watering can .
